    "body": "@thestinger If all Rust code was safe and obeyed borrow semantics then this would be true, but there is plenty of unsafe code that mutates immutable pointers. Do all those unsafe blocks preserve the assumption that `&mut` is unaliased? I don't know, but I doubt it.\n",
