    "created_at": "2013-05-26T19:18:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-05-26T19:48:04Z",
    "body": "@brson: I don't think we'll be able to do this for immutable pointers for a long time - but I doubt there's anything breaking the rules for `&mut` when it comes to function calls (we aren't marking any of the `&` references as `noalias`).\n\nTo break the rules, the function would need to have two borrowed pointer parameters with one or both being `&mut`, and the caller would have to pass the same for both. The result would be one of the pointers potentially not seeing a store done through the `noalias` pointer or vice versa.\n",
